posts.body: Linking directly to the Patreon dropbox is a bad idea.

This kind of logic is also an insanely bad idea. Posting links like this attracts attention, and then they get shared, and the next thing you know shit goes all kinds of sideways. You can't explain away the inevitable by saying "Oh I know. However..." If you know better, please do better. I appreciate the pics, but ways and means matter.
The upload is much appreciated. She just keeps looking better and better.
Mistakes happen. Would rather have dupes than have no new content.

>>986dd168-711b-4429-99f1-26a55d8d21a7
Sometimes the same photo shoot has specific images that are only available to higher tiers. Nigri does that almost every month. Other times they decide some of the images don't make the cut AFTER all the editing is done and they drop them from the set.
Sharing the name would be kind of dumb. Doing that kind of defeats the purpose of security through obscurity. Do what I did: sort by recent posts and start looking. Took me about 15 minutes.

The problem is RARELY the content provider. It's the white knights who whine about it to the content providers. You telling me you trust every anonymous user on milchan? All it takes is for one WK to figure out the board on thothub and it's gone. And then we're scrambling for another source. We need to be uploading that stuff here, or all "two shall take it's place" is pointless.
Hail Hydra.
Check your source and your computer. One of these files set off Ransomware alarms on BitDefender.
